fr.apteryx.imageio.dicom
Class Identifier

Object
  Identifier

public class Identifier
extends Object

Identifiers are used by the Query/Retrieve, Basic Worklist Management and Hanging Protocol Query/Retrieve Service Classes.

Represents either a query or a response after a successful match.

See PS 3.4, Annex C.

Constructor Detail

Identifier

public Identifier(int model,
                  String level)
Creates an Identifier for the Query/Retrieve Service Class with the specified model and level. This constructor should not be called to create an identifier for the Basic Worklist or Hanging Protocol Query/Retrieve Service Class, since the level is not relevant to these service classes.

Parameters:
model - enumerated values: MODEL_QR_PATIENT_ROOT, MODEL_QR_STUDY_ROOT or MODEL_QR_PATIENT_STUDY_ONLY
level - enumerated values: LEVEL_PATIENT, LEVEL_STUDY, LEVEL_SERIES or LEVEL_IMAGE

Identifier

Creates an Identifier for the Worklist Management or Hanging Protocol Query/Retrieve Service Class.

Parameters:
model - enumerated values: MODEL_WL_MODALITY, MODEL_WL_GENERAL_PURPOSE, MODEL_HP
Method Detail

setLevel

public void setLevel(String level)
Convenient replacement of setAttribute to change the Query/Retrieve Level of the identifier. The level of the identifier is not relevant to the Basic Worklist and Hanging Protocol Service Classes.

getLevel

public String getLevel()
Convenient replacement of getAttribute to read the Query/Retrieve Level of the identifier. The level of the identifier is not relevant to the basic Worklist and Hanging Protocol Service Classes.

getModel

public int getModel()
Returns the model of this identifier

requestAttribute

public void requestAttribute(int tag)
Inserts an attribute in the identifier data set with a null value.

This method is called when constructing a query in order to request from the Query/Retrieve SCP to send the value of the specified attribute in the response identifier. The SCP may ignore this request if it does not support querying the specified attribute.

setAttribute

public void setAttribute(int tag,
                         Object value)
Inserts an attribute in the identifier with the specified value.

See DicomMetadata about the restrictions on the class of value. When building an Identifier for a query (C-FIND), attributes of VR DA (date), DT (date-time) and TM (time) can also be specified as ranges using DayRange, DateRange and TimeRange, in order to allow range matching.

If the identifier is used in a query, the SCP may or may not support matching the specified attribute.

getDataSet

public DataSet getDataSet()
